description:
AMAZING udon, fresh tempura!!

I was in a bit of a rush when I came here on my break today but the staff was very friendly and the best part was that they were actually Japanese and there were Japanese people eating here. I always get so shy when I'm around native speakers, I need to get my courage up to bust out nihongo when I'm around people that can actually understand me. ^_^;

Very cool place; I'll be back!
